  <title>Fourth Chapter Quiz</title>

  <task>
    <title>Which of the following is true about the MQ135 Gas Sensor used for air quality monitoring?</title>
    <statement></statement>
    <choices>
      <choice correct="no"><statement>
        <p>It detects methane, butane, and LPG gases.</p>
      </statement>
      <feedback>
      <p>Not Correct! </p>
    </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="yes"><statement>
        <p> The A0 pin of the MQ135 sensor is used to detect the presence of gas in the environment.</p>
      </statement>
      <feedback>
      <p>Correct! </p>
    </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="no"><statement>
        <p>The VCC pin of the MQ135 sensor is connected to the 3.3V pin of the Arduino.</p>
      </statement>
      <feedback>
      <p>Not Correct!</p>
    </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="no"><statement>
        <p>The MQ135 sensor detects ozone gas and is used in water quality monitoring.</p>
      </statement>
      <feedback>
      <p>Not Correct! </p>
    </feedback>
      </choice>
    </choices>
  </task>

  <task>
