  <task>
    <title>Which of the following correctly describes the connection of the Flame Sensor to the Arduino?</title>
    <statement></statement>
    <choices>
      <choice correct="no"><statement>
        <p>The VCC pin of the flame sensor is connected to 3.3V of the Arduino.</p>
      </statement>
      <feedback>
      <p>Not Correct! </p>
    </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="yes"><statement>
        <p>The AO (Analog Out) pin of the flame sensor is connected to A0 pin of the Arduino.</p>
      </statement>
      <feedback>
      <p>Correct! </p>
    </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="no"><statement>
        <p>The GND pin of the flame sensor is connected to the 5V pin of the Arduino.</p>
      </statement>
      <feedback>
      <p>Not Correct!</p>
    </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="no"><statement>
        <p>The AO pin of the flame sensor is connected to the D12 pin of the Arduino.</p>
      </statement>
      <feedback>
      <p>Not Correct! </p>
    </feedback>
      </choice>
    </choices>
  </task>

   <task>
    <title>How are the buzzer and LED connected in the flame detection system?</title>
    <statement></statement>
    <choices>
